React = Declarative UI Programming

With React, you define the target Ul state(s) - not the steps to get there!

Instead, React will figure out & perform the necessary steps

Declarative

Define the goal, not the steps

let content;

if (user.isLoggedIn) { content } else { content <button>Continue</button> <button>Log In</button> }

return content:

JS

Imperative

Define the steps, not the goal

let btn document.querySelector('button');

if (user.isLoggedIn) ( button.textContent 'Continue': } else { } button.textContent Log In':

document.body.append(btn);
