ğŸ” What it is:
StrictMode is a helper component from React.

ğŸ” Why it is used:
It helps you find potential problems in your code.
It does NOT run in production (only during development).

StrictMode warns about:

Unsafe lifecycle methods

Deprecated APIs

Unexpected side effects

Code that may break in future updates

Itâ€™s Reactâ€™s way of saying:

â€œLet me help you write clean and safe React code.â€

2. Import createRoot from ReactDOM
